### MyEStore API Tests
### Install "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) to run these.
### Run in order top-to-bottom. After Login, copy the token into @token below.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5199
@token = PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@otpEmail = mca.sunildhawan@gmail.com

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. AUTH — REGISTER
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1a. Register a new customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "testuser@myestore.com",
  "password": "Test@1234A",
  "confirmPassword": "Test@1234A",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210"
}

###

### 1b. Register an Admin user (for product/order management tests)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Admin",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "admin@myestore.com",
  "password": "Admin@1234A",
  "confirmPassword": "Admin@1234A",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543211"
}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. AUTH — LOGIN  →  copy "token" value into @token above
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2a. Login as test customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@myestore.com",
  "password": "Test@1234A"
}

###

### 2b. Login as admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@myestore.com",
  "password": "Admin@1234A"
}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. AUTH — OTP FLOW
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3a. Request OTP (check mca.sunildhawan@gmail.com inbox)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/send-otp?email={{otpEmail}}

###

### 3b. Verify OTP (replace 123456 with OTP from email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{otpEmail}}",
  "otp": "123456",
  "purpose": "Login"
}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 4. USERS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 4a. Get my profile (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4b. Get all users — admin only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4c. Update my profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Updated",
  "lastName": "Name",
  "phoneNumber": "9876540000"
}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 5. PRODUCTS (public reads, admin writes)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5a. Get all products (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?page=1&pageSize=10

###

### 5b. Create a product — admin token required
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "iPhone 15",
  "description": "Latest Apple smartphone",
  "brand": "Apple",
  "sku": "APL-IP15-128",
  "price": 80000,
  "discountedPrice": 75000,
  "stockQuantity": 50,
  "categoryId": 1,
  "imageUrls": ["https://example.com/iphone15.jpg"],
  "specifications": {
    "RAM": "8GB",
    "Storage": "128GB",
    "Processor": "A16 Bionic"
  },
  "isFeatured": true,
  "isActive": true
}

###

### 5c. Get product by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1

###

### 5d. Search products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/search?query=iphone

###

### 5e. Get products by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/category/Electronics

###

### 5f. Update product stock — admin only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1/stock?quantity=40
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 5g. Update product — admin only
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "iPhone 15 (Updated)",
  "price": 78000,
  "stockQuantity": 45
}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 6. CART
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 6a. View cart
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cart
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6b. Add item to cart
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 2
}

###

### 6c. Update cart item quantity
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/1?quantity=3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6d. Remove one item from cart
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6e. Clear entire cart
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/cart
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 7. ORDERS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 7a. Create an order (cart must have items first — run 6b again before this)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shippingAddress": "123 Sector 22",
  "city": "Chandigarh",
  "state": "Punjab",
  "pINCode": "160022",
  "country": "India",
  "isBillingAddressSameAsShipping": true,
  "paymentMethod": "UPI",
  "couponCode": null,
  "prefferedDeliveryDate": "2026-04-30T00:00:00",
  "deliveryTimeSlot": "10AM-1PM",
  "isGift": false,
  "instructions": "Call before delivery"
}

###

### 7b. Get my orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/my
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7c. Get order by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7d. Get all orders — admin only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7e. Update order status — admin only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1/status?status=Shipped
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7f. Cancel an order
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 8. PAYMENT
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 8a. Process payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payment/process
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": 1,
  "amount": 80000,
  "paymentGateway": "Razorpay",
  "paymentMethod": "UPI"
}

###

### 8b. Verify payment (replace TXN_ID with actual transaction ID from 8a response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/payment/verify/TXN_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 8c. Refund payment — admin only (replace TXN_ID with actual transaction ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payment/refund/TXN_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 9. NEGATIVE / VALIDATION TESTS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 9a. Register with duplicate email — expect 409/400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "testuser@myestore.com",
  "password": "Test@1234A",
  "confirmPassword": "Test@1234A",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210"
}

###

### 9b. Login with wrong password — expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@myestore.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword!"
}

###

### 9c. Access protected route without token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me

###

### 9d. Add cart item with invalid quantity — expect 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 0
}

###

### 9e. Create product without admin role — expect 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Hack Product",
  "price": 100,
  "stockQuantity": 1,
  "categoryId": 1,
  "brand": "X",
  "sku": "X-001"
}

###

### 9f. Get non-existent product — expect 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/99999
